
*******************************************************************************
input	- 	input string from keyboard with optional prompt
*******************************************************************************

  This command inputs fields of characters from the keyboard and 
  stores them into one or more string variables.  This procedure allows an
  input prompt to be displayed on the command line.  The input fields
  are delimited by a setable delimiter character.  The default delimiter
  is a comma.  The routine stores the values into as many return values
  that are given and ignores the rest of the input line. 

  Usage  -  input[('inputprompt'[,'delimiter'])]:var1,var2,...

	    where inputprompt is a string.
            delimiter is the delimiter character between input fields.
	    variables are defined string variables.

  Examples;

    input:b				input into variable b.
    input('enter a number:'):a		input into a with prompt.
    input('x and y coordinates'):x,y    input into two variables with prompt
					example input  12,15

    input('enter lastname:firstname',':'):last,first   input two names 
						       delimited by ':'
					example input  lasslo:rick
